control_flows_csharp.q:
What is the output of the following code?
int i = 5;
if (i > 0) goto Label;
Console.WriteLine("Not printed");
Label: Console.WriteLine(i);

What is the value of `x` after this loop?
int x = 0;
for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) { if (i == 3) continue; x += i; }

What is the output?
int i = 0;
while (i < 3) { if (i++ == 1) continue; Console.Write(i); }

You see this code in legacy system:
Label1: Console.WriteLine("X");
if (condition) goto Label1;
What kind of loop is this simulating?

What is the output?
for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++)
    for (int j = 0; j < 2; j++)
        if (i == 1 && j == 1) break;
        else Console.Write(i + "" + j);

